        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 21 at 3:02PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 301 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crossroads Village, or near Clio, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flint, North Branch, Mayville, Columbiaville, Mount Morris,
Otisville, Otter Lake, Clifford, Crossroads Village, Beecher,
Genesee, Silverwood, Thetford Township, Kings Mill, and Fostoria.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
